This paper primarily focuses on the creation of interconnection networks in the context of the Internet of Things (IoT), which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also uses game theory to model the behavior of individual devices in the network, which suggests that it could be categorized under game theory and economics (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the network in terms of cost functions, which could be categorized under signal processing (cs.SI) or information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical foundations of IoT infrastructure construction, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
